{"title":"Velo Orange Updates Rugged Off-Road Tourer in New Piolet Frameset","link":"https://bikerumor.com/velo-orange-updates-off-road-tourer-piolet-frameset/","date":1692113400000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet hero side shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot.jpeg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-hero-side-shot-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Straight outta Mayland on Monday, <a href=\"https://velo-orange.com/\" target=\"_blank\">makers of bike stuff</a> that are focused more on SPH (Smiles Per Hour) than MPH (Miles Per Hour), Velo Orange announced they’re opening the pre-orders for their much anticipated, <a href=\"https://velo-orange.com/products/vo-piolet-frameset\" target=\"_blank\">newly updated</a>, Piolet Frameset. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Piolet is French for<s> pilot</s> ice axe. If you didn’t know, now ya do. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new frameset is now coming in a striking Metallic Moss color, and if you move quickly, you can get one for yourself at a discount of $795 (regular retail is $925), with expected deliveries in early September. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet rear dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-dropouts.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Velo Orange New thru-axle rear dropouts</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Piolet Frameset is Velo Orange’s dirt tourer, bikepacker, and rough-road riding frame. Fire roads, gravel roads, double track, single track… it can do it all. Velo Orange says it’s “built to be sturdy, simple, and very capable”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet head badge and fork crown\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-head-badge-and-fork-crown.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Segmented non-suspension corrected fork</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now equipped with thru-axles front and rear, the new Piolet frameset uses double-butted chromoly steel, with a triple-butted, non-suspension corrected fork to not only reduce weight but add strength. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"417\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681-800x417.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet rear monostay\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681-800x417.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681-297x155.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681-120x63.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681-768x400.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-rear-monostay-e1692111639681.jpeg 1276w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Piolet frameset also incorporates a unique mono-stay, wishbone where the seatstays come together, purposely complimenting the beautiful segmented fork. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780-800x395.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet bottom bracket\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780-800x395.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780-297x147.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780-120x59.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780-768x379.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-bottom-bracket-e1692111764780.jpeg 1276w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is covered in bosses for any packing, water, accessory, or fender situation you throw at it. So, you could set it up as a hardcore bikepacker, or a traditional bag tourer…your call. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet handlebar bags headbadge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-handlebar-bags-headbadge.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Drop bars with stem bags </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Velo Orange says the Piolet will handle similar to an XC mountain bike with a lean in the touring direction, feeling at home with flat or drop bars equipped. The non-suspension corrected fork handles predictably with or without a load. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Piolet will be available in four sizes, S, M, L, and XL. The small size is designed around 26″x2.4″ tires, with the medium, large, and x-large being designed around 29″x2.4″ (or 27.5″x2.8″). </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Velo Orange Piolet Frame Features/Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frameset material:</strong> 4130 double-butted chrome-moly</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> 1 1/8″ threadless, heat-treated triple butted</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheel Size:</strong> 29″ &amp; 27.5+ (M, L, XL), 26″ (S)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tire:</strong> 29″ x 2.4″ or 27.5 x 2.6″ (M, L, XL), 26″ x 2.4 (S)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear Spacing:</strong> 12x142mm thru-axle</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Front Spacing</strong>: 12x100mm thru-axle</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottom Bracket:</strong> English threaded 73mm, mountain cranksets only</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Brakes:</strong> 160 – 180mm disc rotor size, IS mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost:</strong> 27.2mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Front Derailleur Size:</strong> 28.6mm, bottom pull/bottom swing</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Water bottle mounts:</strong> 3 sets on the frame, 2 sets on fork blades</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fender bosses:</strong> seat stay bridge, chainstay bridge, under the fork crown</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Dropouts</strong>: Vertical with triple eyelets</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lowrider thru bosses on the fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 sets of seat stay rack eyelets</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replaceable stainless steel derailleur hanger</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Paint</strong>: Metallic Moss</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Piolet Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-geometry.jpeg\"><img width=\"438\" height=\"339\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-geometry.jpeg\" alt=\"Velo Orange Piolet geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-geometry.jpeg 438w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-geometry-297x230.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Velo-Orange-Piolet-geometry-120x93.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Do yourself a big favor and drop over to Velo Orange and check out all of the amazing and unique bike love they have going on over there, by hitting the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://velo-orange.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Velo-Orange.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/velo-orange-updates-off-road-tourer-piolet-frameset/\">Velo Orange Updates Rugged Off-Road Tourer in New Piolet Frameset</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4e165a3d4689ae342f10e356a0226dc8105e89a0ef8049bf60357ce9e6afac35","category":"Cycling"}